<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p { margin-bottom: 10px; } </mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3"> 
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              margin-top:2px;
            ">Did you know the President of the United States receives a top-secret briefing on national security every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>In today’s edition:</strong> </p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Biden’s pardons and commute</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ Prisoners swap</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left: 10px;
            ">→ State of emergency in Columbia</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- breaking news1  -->
    <!-- /breaking news 1 -->
    <mj-spacer height="10px" />
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          padding-bottom:8px;
          color:#4D3060;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #4D3060;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
               
            ">SPOTLIGHT</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">Democrat states sue Trump</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-jan-22-1.png" alt="Democrat states sue Trump" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><strong>Summary: Democrat states sue Trump over birthright citizenship order, which violates the 14th Amendment.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Donald Trump’s executive order to end birthright citizenship has triggered legal battles. 24 Democratic states are suing, arguing that the order violates the 14th Amendment, which guarantees citizenship to all born on US soil. The lawsuit was filed in Massachusetts, which maintains that the order exceeds presidential authority and undermines constitutional rights (<a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-01-2025-h1-1-details-of-the-lawsuit" target="_blank">details of the lawsuit</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">The order denies citizenship to children born in the US to parents who are undocumented or temporarily in the country. The argument for it is a disputed interpretation of the Amendment’s “subject to the jurisdiction thereof” clause. Legal opponents argue that this interpretation conflicts with longstanding precedent (<a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-22-01-2025-h1-2-executive-order" target="_blank">executive order</a>).</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column> 
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>